messages.content:
Here's a simple HTML file that will display the text "h4k3r" in the center of the page in a large font size. After 3 seconds, it will redirect the user to the `/hello` path. You can just copy the entire code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Redirect Example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #282c34;
            color: white;
            font-size: 10em; /* Very big font size */
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="message">h4k3r</div>
    <script>
        // Wait for 3 seconds (3000 milliseconds) before redirecting
        setTimeout(function() {
            window.location.href = '/hello';
        }, 3000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
1. **HTML Structure**: The document includes basic HTML structure and includes the necessary `<head>` and `<body>` tags.
2. **CSS Styles**: The CSS styles center the text both vertically and horizontally on the page and set a large font size. The background color and text color are also defined.
3. **JavaScript Redirect**: The JavaScript uses `setTimeout` to redirect to `/hello` after a 3-second delay. 

Just save the code in an `index.html` file (or any filename with `.html` extension) and open it in your web browser to see it in action!
